caption: Good place for fresh burgers and fries made just how you want it. A bit pricey, but you get what you pay for. Staff is always helpful and prompt.  UPDATE: After being a regular customer for some time, I finally felt compelled to downgrade my review by a star. It started when they changed their menu appearance, and simultaneously their pricing and loyalty program. Evidently they stopped giving a "combo" discount (for fries and a drink), so what used to cost me $15.57 now costs me $17.00. Of course I earn Bite Club points now (yay?), but it takes quite a few purchases to get anything from it. I find the quality is still great, and service pretty good, but it's now in a "premium" lunch cost category (for a burger!), and I'm simply not going to frequent it as often. Sorry, I consider this an Epic fail (get it?) to its loyal customers.
